sentences.english: This study is significant for generation of ultra-short optical pulse chain at high repetition rate.

sentences.english: Across the industry, occupancy rates have dropped about 10 percent Carew said.

sentences.english: The treaty fixed the permitted ratio of government debt-to-GDP at 60 percent.
sentences.chinese: 条约规定政府债务率最高可为60%。

sentences.english: They looked at long-term sick leave (of over 90 days) and hospital admission rates.
sentences.chinese: 他们关注的重点是超过90天的长时间病假和住院率。

sentences.english: No data are available to support a correlation between RGV and adverse event rates.

sentences.english: The influence of absorbing type refrigerating machine upon enorgysaving rate of the triplex cogeneration system to be very little.

sentences.english: Erythrocyte sedimentation rate was slow in perinatal newborn.

sentences.english: The linear density and unevenness of PET spun staple fiber were measured by vibration method.

sentences.english: The juice yield decreased with treating time postponed.

sentences.english: And at what rate do you discount those cash flows?

sentences.english: Migraines are one of the few neurological disorders to subside with age.

sentences.english: Paradoxically, the principle of voluntary join caused a low attendance of farmers.

sentences.english: In order to attain the certain lump coal rate, the key is reasonable picks-lacing.

sentences.english: The use of gastric emptying rate of phenol red measured response in each group pyloric sphincter pressure in rats.
